Coke woos McDonald ' s in soda wars - NYT . Coca - Cola Co is seeking to banish soft drinks produced by Dr Pepper / Seven Up Inc from thousands of McDonald ' s Corp restaurants , the New York Times said . In Tuesday ' s edition , the Times said Coca - Cola has offered so - called " exclusive awards " to McDonald ' s restaurants owners , including several thousand that carry the Dr Pepper brand . Dr Pepper / Seven Up is a subsidiary of Cadbury Schweppes Plc . In exchange for selling only Coca - Cola products , Coke has offered McDonald ' s franchisees between 200 and 600 free gallons of soda syrup for each restaurant , enough to make between 30 , 000 and 90 , 000 drinks per restaurant . The Times said Dr Pepper / Seven Up Chief Executive Todd Stitzer declined to comment on the matter , which originally was reported in the industry newsletter , Beverage Digest . ( ( - - New York Newsdesk 212 - 859 - 1610 ) ) 
